ODHA (Orang Dengan HIV AIDS) is a person who got infected by human
immunodeficiency virus. This virus is a blood-borne virus which is transmitted via sexual intercourse, shared intravenous drug, and mother-to-child transmission.

So, WE should remove the stigma about discriminating people with HIV/AIDS and give them our love and empathy, not discrimination and hate. 
Today, 1st of December is World HIV/AIDS day.
I, Billy Priyanto, so proud of joining all Ambassador of Public Health of AMSA-Indonesia to share this fact.
